"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806625","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-01-02","<p>The Registry Trust which maintains the Register of Judgments, Orders and Fines collates and publishes quarterly reports including analysis and commentary on County Court Judgments on behalf of the Lord Chancellor. The statistics are available at <a href="http://www.trustonline.org.uk" target="_blank">www.trustonline.org.uk</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The Ministry of Justice publishes quarterly statistics available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/civil-justice-statistics-quarterly-july-to-september-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/civil-justice-statistics-quarterly-july-to-september-2017</a></p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2018-01-02T09:37:47.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806625/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806625/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806625/answer","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806625/answer/previousversion/32534","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-14","County Courts: Judgements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what recent assessment he has made of the trends in the level of county court judgements; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","119701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806626","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-21","<p>The Government welcomes the United Nations’ efforts to understand and address the problem of illicit financial flows in Africa and is committed to supporting African countries to effectively tackle this issue. The Government provides financial and advisory support to the Eastern and Southern Africa Anti-Money Laundering Group and provides technical assistance to many countries across the continent in areas such as anti-corruption, anti-money laundering, tax transparency and public financial management. This support includes capacity building for Financial Intelligence Units and tax administrations, including in relation to exchange of information for tax purposes and implementation of the outcomes of the Base Erosion and Profit Shifting project.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-12-21T10:53:24.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806626/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806626/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806626/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-14","Corruption: Africa","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment his Department has made of the implications for his policies of the report of United Nations Economic Commission for Africa's High Level Panel on Illicit Financial Flows from Africa.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","119702"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806627","Department for Education","false","2017-12-19","<p>The school moved to its permanent site in September 2017 and the Education and Skills Funding Agency is currently commissioning the remaining works on site, for completion in 2018.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-19T17:53:13.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806627/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806627/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806627/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-14","Parkfield School Bournemouth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 5 July to Question 2169 on Parkfield School, Bournemouth, whether that project is now complete.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","119703"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806628","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-19","<p>The National Shipbuilding Strategy set out that we would seek to ensure the UK's long term operational advantage and freedom of action by strengthening the nation's industrial shipbuilding base, including the ability to design, build and integrate warships.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-12-19T15:43:54.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806628/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806628/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806628/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-14","Warships: Shipbuilding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons there are no key industrial capabilities with regard to the UK complex warship building industry identified in the National Shipbuilding Strategy.","false","Biography information for Mr Paul Sweeney","Glasgow North East","Mr Paul Sweeney","119704"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806629","Department of Health","false","2017-12-21","<p>The Government has made no assessment of the potential effect of minimum unit pricing (MUP) of alcohol on reducing the incidence of cancer or the number of cancer deaths. MUP and its effects will continue to remain under review pending the impact of its implementation in Scotland.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","119707","2017-12-21T16:27:03.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806629/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806629/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806629/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-14","Alcoholic Drinks: Minimum Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment his Department has made of the potential effect of minimum unit pricing on alcohol on reducing the incidence of cancer.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","119705"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806630","Department of Health","false","2017-12-21","<p>The use of tamoxifen to reduce the risk of breast cancer for those with a family history of the disease is one of a number of options recommended for consideration by patients and clinicians within the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) Clinical Guideline 164 (last updated during March 2017). The guideline identifies a number of patient groups in a number of different ways, such as risk level, pre/post menopause and whether or not patients have osteoporosis. The provision of tamoxifen is a matter for local clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) and NHS England expects CCGs to take account of NICE guidelines and local population needs when making commissioning decisions.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England recognises that bisphosphonates may have benefits for some women in preventing secondary breast cancer, however the provision of biophosphates is a matter for CCGs. NICE is considering the evidence on bisphosphonates and will be updating its clinical guidelines to take account of their use. We understand that this work is due to complete in 2018. However, subject to local commissioning policy, clinicians are already able to prescribe bisphosphonates for the treatment of secondary breast cancer where they judge it to be the most clinically appropriate treatment for an individual patient.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-12-21T16:30:44.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806630/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806630/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806630/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-14","Breast Cancer: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what plans he has for the NHS to prescribe (a) tamoxifen to reduce the risk of breast cancer for those with a family history of the disease and (b) bisphosphonates to reduce the risk of secondary breast cancer in menopausal women.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","119706"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806631","Department of Health","false","2017-12-21","<p>The Government has made no assessment of the potential effect of minimum unit pricing (MUP) of alcohol on reducing the incidence of cancer or the number of cancer deaths. MUP and its effects will continue to remain under review pending the impact of its implementation in Scotland.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","119705","2017-12-21T16:27:04.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806631/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806631/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806631/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-14","Alcoholic Drinks: Minimum Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of minimum unit pricing of alcohol on the number of cancer deaths.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","119707"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806632","Department of Health","false","2017-12-21","<p>On 5 December 2017, Health Education England published a comprehensive cancer workforce plan, developed with NHS England. This plan focuses on the actions needed to ensure that there is enough staff with the right skills to deliver the activity set out in the Cancer Taskforce Strategy, by 2021. The plan includes investment in 300 reporting radiographers by 2021 but it is not just about increasing numbers, it is about supporting staff to develop new skills and enabling them to work differently.</p><p> </p><p>The Cancer Workforce Plan is available at:</p><p><a href="https://hee.nhs.uk/sites/default/files/documents/Cancer%20Workforce%20Plan.pdf" target="_blank">https://hee.nhs.uk/sites/default/files/documents/Cancer%20Workforce%20Plan.pdf</a></p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-12-21T16:12:27.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806632/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806632/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806632/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-14","Breast Cancer: Diagnosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what plans he has for (a) workforce planning and (b) investment to ensure there is  diagnostic capacity for breast cancer in the NHS.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","119708"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806633","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-19","<p>HMS OCEAN entered service in 1998 with a specified service life, based on her build specification, of 20 years. Work on HMS OCEAN's refit began in December 2012 and was completed in August 2014. The timing of the refit was driven by the mandatory requirement to revalidate the ship's safety and environmental certification. The decommissioning date of 2018 is the same as that planned at the time of this refit.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-12-19T15:01:02.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806633/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806633/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806633/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-14","HMS Ocean","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the decision to decommission HMS Ocean in 2018 was finalised before the refit of that warship in 2014.","false","Biography information for Mr Paul Sweeney","Glasgow North East","Mr Paul Sweeney","119709"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806634","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-19","<p>The Department will be reviewing and paying arrears that are due to claimants affected. These payments will be paid from 21/10/2014 which is the Departments mandatory statutory requirement with regard to payment of arrears when a court or tribunal establishes the meaning of a legislative provision. Under this provision DWP will pay arrears from the date of the court or tribunal decision, which in this case is the 21/10/2014. The rule was most recently confirmed by Parliament in section 27 of the Social Security Act 1998, which received Royal Assent on 21 May 1998.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","119797","2017-12-19T12:14:06.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806634/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806634/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806634/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-14","Employment and Support Allowance: Maladministration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 7 December 2017 to Question 116610, whether his Department intends to pay to each claimant whose entitlements were miscalculated between 2011 and 2014 the full amount dating back to when the miscalculation was made.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","119710"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806635","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-19","<p>The initiative at Birkenhead Jobcentre brought together information from energy suppliers to help the vulnerable and those facing difficulties in meeting their energy costs.</p><p> </p><p>The initiative informed a DWP produced factsheet which covers saving money on household bills, advice for those struggling with debt and details about basic bank accounts. The factsheet also signposts to further sources of help and support through a range of websites including The Money Advice Service.</p><p> </p><p>The DWP factsheet is available to all Work Coaches across the Jobcentre Plus network.</p><p> </p><p>We are unable to confirm the numbers used or the number of claimants availing themselves of the support.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","119713 ; 119717","2017-12-19T14:33:53.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806635/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806635/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806635/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-14","Jobcentres","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer on 3 July 2017 to Question 882, whether the reformed welfare contract piloted at Birkenhead Jobcentre Plus is now operational across the whole Jobcentre Plus network.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","119711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806636","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-19","<p>The National Shipbuilding Strategy lays the foundations for a modern and efficient shipbuilding sector capable of meeting the country's future defence and security needs.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","119714 ; 119716","2017-12-19T16:15:11.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806636/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806636/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806636/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-14","Warships: Shipbuilding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the National Shipbuilding Strategy is planned to achieve upper quartile performance in the UK complex warship building industry as previously set out in the Terms of Business Agreement signed in 2009 between his Department and the company currently known as BAE Surface Systems Ships Ltd.","false","Biography information for Mr Paul Sweeney","Glasgow North East","Mr Paul Sweeney","119712"
