"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806665","Department of Health","false","2017-12-21","<p>Registered Medical Practitioners (RMP) are legally required, under the Abortion Act 1967, as amended, to notify the Chief Medical Officer of every abortion performed in England and Wales on form HSA4. The forms are used to check that abortions are performed legally and for the compilation of abortion statistics. The recording of the patient’s National Health Service number is not necessary for this purpose. However, the RMP must provide a patient reference number that can identify the patient. This could be the patient’s hospital/clinic number or their NHS number. If a patient reference number is not available, the patient’s full name should be recorded on the HSA4 form.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-12-21T15:57:06.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806665/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806665/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806665/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-14","Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, for what reasons guidance for doctors completing the HSA4 form states that recording the NHS number is optional when abortion providers are mandated by the NHS Number Programme Implementation Policy 2008 to record the NHS numbers for their patients.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","119741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806666","Department of Health","false","2017-12-20","<p>This information is not collected centrally.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","119784","2017-12-20T11:26:54.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806666/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806666/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806666/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-14","Foetal Death","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what information his Department holds on the number of fetuses which were (a) incinerated, (b) cremated and (c) buried after induced abortions at (i) NHS hospitals and (ii) independent abortion providers in 2016.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","119742"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806667","Department for International Development","false","2017-12-21","<p>DFID has robust monitoring and evaluation procedures to ensure UK taxpayers’ money is achieving the results we expect of it. Precise monitoring arrangements vary by project; however progress is always reviewed by DFID, on an annual basis. All of our reviews demonstrate confidence in the quality of MSI’s services in developing countries.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-12-21T15:27:17.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806667/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806667/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806667/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-12-14","Marie Stopes International","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what recent assessment she has made of her Department's funding to Marie Stopes International in developing countries, in light of the suspension of Marie Stopes’ abortion services in the UK.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","119743"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806668","Home Office","false","2017-12-19","<p>The Home Office does not hold the informaiton in the format requested.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-12-19T17:31:01.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806668/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806668/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806668/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-14","Immigration Controls: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many Palestinians living in Israel and Palestine have been refused entry to the UK in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Matt Western","Warwick and Leamington","Matt Western","119744"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806669","Home Office","false","2017-12-19","<p>This information can be found on the attached link which is published on www.gov.uk</p><p><br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-july-to-september-2017/list-of-tables#admissions." target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-july-to-september-2017/list-of-tables#admissions.</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-12-19T17:29:53.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806669/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806669/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806669/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-14","Immigration Controls: Israel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many Israeli citizens have been refused entry to the UK in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Matt Western","Warwick and Leamington","Matt Western","119745"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806670","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-19","<p>The Work and Pensions Secretary of State has a duty to review the Lower Benefit Cap levels once in each Parliament with regard to the national economic situation and any other matters he considers relevant, as set out in the 2016 Welfare Reform and Work Act. New lower and tiered Benefit Cap rates were introduced from November 2016 prior to the election in June 2017. We intend to review the Lower Benefit Cap during this Parliament.</p><p> </p><p>For context, outside of London, around 4 in 10 households have net earnings less than the £20,000 cap level. In London around 4 in 10 households have net earnings of less than the £23,000 cap level.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-12-19T16:39:48.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806670/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806670/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806670/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-14","Social Security Benefits: Uprating","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the change in the real terms value of the maximum amount of benefit entitlement as a result of inflation since the introduction of the benefit cap in November 2016.","false","Biography information for Ged Killen","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Ged Killen","119746"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806671","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-20","<p>I refer the right honourable member to my answer of 7 November 2017 (PQ 110748).</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-12-20T16:34:52.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806671/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806671/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806671/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-14","Equitable Life Assurance Society: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the number of Equitable Life policyholders who have received payments (a) of less than a quarter of their relative losses, (b) more than a quarter of their relative losses and (c) totalling their relative losses.","false","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","119747"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806672","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-21","<p>Highways England are serious about tackling cases of evasion. They use an Automatic Number Plate Recognition (ANPR) system which is capable of capturing non-UK vehicle registration marks and they apply effective penalty and recovery processes that have been proven elsewhere, such as London’s congestion charging and Dublin’s M50 toll schemes. Ultimately a European debt recovery agency is used to pursue and recover outstanding charges from non-UK vehicles that evade paying the Crossing charge.</p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-12-21T09:01:30.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806672/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806672/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806672/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-14","Dartford Tunnel: Tolls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to pursue outstanding payments owed by the drivers of vehicles from non-UK EU Member States who have travelled through the Dartford tunnel.","false","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","119748"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806673","Home Office","false","2017-12-21","<p>The Government’s consultation on new legislation on offensive and dangerous weapons closed on 9 December 2017. We are currently considering the responses and the Government will publish its response to the consultation in early 2018.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2017-12-21T17:18:45.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806673/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806673/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806673/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-14","Offensive Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment he has made of the effect of the proposals in the consultation on offensive and dangerous weapons, published in October 2017, to prohibit the private ownership of items on the offensive weapons list on people who currently possess such items; and what guidance her Department plans to issue to people on the legality of continued possession of such items.","false","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon","119749"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806674","Scotland Office","false","2017-12-19","<p>The total Scotland Office spend on events in 2016/17 amounts to £61,188.38.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-12-19T16:03:39.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806674/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806674/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806674/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-12-14","Scotland Office: Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, pursuant to the Answer of 14 December 2017 to Question 118330 on Scotland Office: official hospitality, what the events spend of his Department was in 2016-17","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","119750"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806675","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-12-21","<p>Paragraph 52 of the Joint Report recognises the identity and citizenship rights of the people of Northern Ireland under the Belfast Agreement and the associated British-Irish Agreement (the Agreement between the Government of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland and the Government of Ireland, done at Belfast on 10 April 1998), which gives effect to those rights under international law. Section 149 of the Equality Act 2010 does not extend to Northern Ireland and nor does it impact the rights that Ireland affords its citizens. There is a similar public sector duty in section 75 of the Northern Ireland Act 1998.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-12-21T16:08:36.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806675/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806675/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806675/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-12-14","Nationality: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, with reference to paragraph 52 of the Joint Report of the Negotiators of the European Union and the United Kingdom Government, published on 8 December 2017, what assessment he has made of the compatibility of a Withdrawal Agreement respecting the rights, opportunities, and identity of one part of the UK population with section 149 of the Equality Act 2010.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","119751"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806676","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-19","<p>The Department has effective processes to identify individual training needs, resulting in role specific learning, including the provision of excellent customer service. This is underpinned by workplace consolidation activities observed by managers, which supports individuals to continuously improve and develop their skills and knowledge.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-12-19T14:38:42.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806676/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806676/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806676/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-14","Jobcentre Plus: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps his Department has taken to ensure staff at a JobCentre Plus are adequately trained in their duties to improve the level of claimant satisfaction rates.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","119752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806677","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-19","<p>This information is not readily available at constituency level and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is continually working to improve the accuracy of benefit entitlement awards. This includes working with Assessment Providers to ensure claimants receive high quality assessments and improving the way further evidence is collected to ensure all relevant information about an individual’s needs is available to decision makers at the earliest opportunity. Furthermore, the recruitment of approximately 150 Presenting Officers provides valuable insight into why decisions are overturned on appeal and is helping us identify improvements throughout the claimant journey.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-12-19T12:08:07.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806677/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806677/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806677/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-14","Work Capability Assessment: Redcar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of work capability assessment decisions overturned in Redcar in each of the last five years where figures are available; and what steps he is taking to improve the accuracy of benefit entitlement awards.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","119753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806678","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-19","<p>The policies of the British Government on Sudan have not changed as a result of the UK-Sudan Trade and Investment Forum. As part of our phased increase in direct engagement with the Government of Sudan, we continue to consider opportunities to promote trade with Sudan. Trade can help open up closed off political and economic systems, and thereby help to improve the human rights situation. Sudan remains a Foreign and Commonwealth Office Human Rights Priority Country and improving human rights is a key objective in our engagement with Sudan. The UK-Sudan Trade and Investment Forum was a private event, organised and funded by Developing Markets Associates, in cooperation with the Sudanese Embassy in London.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-12-19T14:22:11.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806678/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806678/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806678/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-14","Sudan: Overseas Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the implications for his Department's policies on Sudan of the as a result of the meeting of the UK-Sudan Trade and Investment Forum, held in London on 12 December 2017.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","119754"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806679","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-20","<p>Nobody is sanctioned where they can demonstrate they had good reason for failing to attend an appointment. Each case is considered individually, taking into account individual and prevailing circumstances. Where adverse weather conditions make it unreasonable for someone to attend, no sanction would be applied.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-12-20T15:39:14.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806679/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806679/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806679/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-14","Social Security Benefits: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he is taking to ensure that benefit claimants who cannot attend appointments due to adverse weather conditions will not be sanctioned.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","119755"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806680","Department of Health","false","2017-12-19","<p>No specific estimate has been made. The majority of patients receiving treatment for rheumatoid arthritis are managed in outpatient settings where data collection is not mandated.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-12-19T17:23:31.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806680/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806680/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806680/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-14","Arthritis: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate his Department has made of the number of patients receiving treatment for arthritis in (a) South Tees NHS Trust, (b) the North East and (c) England.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","119756"
