"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806037","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-18","<p>The Ministry of Justice is not responsible for meeting such costs in privately managed prisons. As per my Answer to Question 117497, the costs of any re-locking in privately managed prisons in 2016/17 were met by the providers.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-12-18T14:18:17.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806037/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806037/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806037/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-13","Prisons: Locks and Keys","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 11 December 2017 to Question 117497, what the cost was of relocking prisons by the private contractor in 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","119246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806038","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-19","<p>The information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>The deployment of staff between prisons on detached duty is a regular and normal part of prison resourcing. It allows staff to be allocated from prisons with the capacity to provide them, to those where additional staffing is required. Since October 2013, national detached duty has been coordinated centrally. Detached duty has taken place every day since this date.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-12-19T13:04:37.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806038/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806038/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806038/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-13","Prison Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many days of detached duty have been worked by prison officers in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","119247"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806039","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-18","<p>The information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>The deployment of staff between prisons on detached duty is a regular and normal part of prison resourcing. It allows staff to be allocated from prisons with the capacity to provide them, to those where additional staffing is required. Since October 2013, national detached duty has been coordinated centrally. Detached duty has taken place every day since this date.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-12-18T14:18:06.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806039/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806039/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806039/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-13","Prison Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many days of detached duty have been worked by prison officers in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","119248"
