"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806073","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-12-18","<p>As I stated in my previous response on 27 November 2017, responsibility for prisons in Northern Ireland is primarily a devolved area. Under the devolution of policing and justice in 2010, the Department of Justice (DoJ) is solely responsible for management of the prison estate.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2017-12-18T12:33:36.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806073/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806073/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806073/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-12-13","Magilligan Prison","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, if he will take steps during the absence of a devolved administration to discuss with the Department of Justice the rebuilding of the Prison at Magilligan in County Londonderry.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","119276"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806074","Department of Health","false","2017-12-21","<p>NHS Resolution has supplied the following information:</p><p> </p><p>NHS Resolution holds information relating to claims notified to it against pre-defined injury, cause and specialty codes. NHS Resolution has used the following search terms:</p><p> </p><p>The total number of clinical claims where one of the injuries was ‘stroke’ and one of the causes was ‘Failure/Delay Diagnosis’ or ‘Wrong Diagnosis’, received 1 December 2016 to 30 November 2017 was 35.</p><p> </p><p>NHS Resolution does not have a code for mistreatment of atrial fibrillation so it has undertaken a search of the number of clinical claims where one of the injuries was ‘stroke’ and ‘atrial fibrillation’ was mentioned in the incident details reported, received 1 December 2016 to 30 November 2017.</p><p> </p><p>NHS Resolution has advised that it cannot provide the number of claims because to do so might lead to the identification of an individual.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-12-21T15:41:10.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806074/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806074/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806074/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-13","NHS: Negligence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many clinical negligence claims relating to a stroke have been made against NHS trusts due to (a) a misdiagnosis and (b) mistreatment of atrial fibrillation in the last twelve months.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","119277"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806075","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-12-21","<p>Departments routinely publish their expenditure on contractors in their Annual Report and Accounts.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><ol><li><p>The cost to the Department of using contractors in 2016-17 is published in the 2017 Annual Report and Accounts.</p></li><li><p>The cost to the Department of using contractors in 2017-18 will be found in the 2018 Annual Report and Accounts which will be published next year.</p></li><li><p>There is no specific forecast for the cost of using private contractors for future years as contractors are used in order to meet short-term/immediate pressures. The Department ensures it has sufficient funds in order to deliver its objectives.</p></li></ol><p><strong> </strong></p><p>All contractors are provided by approved government suppliers.</p><p> </p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-12-21T12:38:37.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806075/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806075/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806075/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-12-13","Department for Exiting the European Union: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what estimate he has made of the cost to the public purse of using private contractors in his Department in the (a) 2016-17, (b) current and (c) next financial year.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","119278"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806076","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-18","<p>The number of people with epilepsy who were previously in receipt of Disability Living Allowance and have undergone a review to assess their eligibility for Personal Independence Payment applied for mandatory reconsideration of the decision from<br></p><p>(a) April 2013 to October 2017 (55 months) was 11,550.</p><p> </p><p>(b) October 2016 to October 2017 (12 months) was 6040.</p><p> </p><p>Data is taken from the DWP PIP computer system’s management information.</p><p> </p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-12-18T11:42:22.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806076/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806076/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806076/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-13","Personal Independence Payment: Epilepsy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people with epilepsy who were previously in receipt of disability living allowance and have undergone a review to assess their eligibility for personal independence payments applied for mandatory reconsideration of the decision from (a) April 2013 to October 2017 and (b) October 2016 to October 2017.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","119279"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806077","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-18","<p>The number of people with epilepsy who were previously in receipt of Disability Living Allowance and have undergone a review to assess their eligibility for Personal Independence Payment appealed the decision at tribunal from</p><p> </p><p>(a) April 2013 to October 2017 (55 months) is 4770.</p><p> </p><p>(b) October 2016 to October 2017 (12 months) is 2500.</p><p> </p><p>Data taken from the DWP PIP computer system’s management information.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-12-18T11:46:09.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806077/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806077/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806077/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-13","Personal Independence Payment: Epilepsy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people with epilepsy who were previously in receipt of disability living allowance and have undergone a review to assess their eligibility for personal independence payments appealed the decision at tribunal from (a) April 2013 to October 2017 (b) October 2016 to October 2017.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","119280"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806078","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-19","<p>Since 1 April 2017, the Carbon Savings Community Obligation is no longer part of the Energy Company Obligation (ECO). However, we introduced a rural safeguard of 15% in the Carbon Emissions Reduction Obligation (CERO) of the current ECO scheme. In addition, the scoring mechanism under ECO is such that it incentivises delivery of measures in properties off the gas grid. Early next year we intend to consult on proposals for the future Energy Company Obligation which are expected to run from October 2018 to March 2022. The consultation will include proposals on rural delivery and on moving to a 100% focus on vulnerable and low income households.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","119284 ; 119286","2017-12-19T14:01:54.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806078/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806078/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806078/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-13","Energy Companies Obligation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if he will change the Energy Company Obligation to give higher priority to helping rural communities that are off the mains gas grid.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","119281"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806079","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-18","<p>Whilst Defra collects information on the number of livestock units in England, no information is collected on whether these units are intensive.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-12-18T17:11:24.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806079/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806079/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806079/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-13","Livestock Industry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent estimate he has made of the number of intensive livestock units in the UK.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","119282"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806080","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-21","<p>Antibiotic resistant bacteria data are collected through two methods of surveillance (clinical surveillance and monitoring). The surveillance programme serves to monitor resistance in a number of drug/bug combinations, which are a priority for human and animal health, rather than to monitor trends by type of farming systems. The harmonised monitoring produces results that are intended to be representative at a country level. The clinical surveillance relies on voluntary submission of samples by private veterinarians for diagnostic investigations to the network of government laboratories, and generates a useful indication of some of the resistance seen in the overall livestock population.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The latest data published in 2016 shows that overall, the rates of resistance have remained relatively stable for most of the bacteria and antibiotics tested. However, the level of resistance in <em>E.coli</em> found in chickens has started to decrease. All results from the Veterinary Medicines Directorate’s surveillance and monitoring activities are published annually in the UK-VARSS report - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/veterinary-antimicrobial-resistance-and-sales-surveillance-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/veterinary-antimicrobial-resistance-and-sales-surveillance-2016</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-12-21T13:56:19.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806080/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806080/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806080/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-13","Livestock: Antibiotics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment he has made of (a) the level of antibiotic resistant bacteria associated with intensive livestock units in the UK and (b) how this level of antibiotic resistant bacteria has changed in the past five years.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","119283"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806081","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-19","<p>Since 1 April 2017, the Carbon Savings Community Obligation is no longer part of the Energy Company Obligation (ECO). However, we introduced a rural safeguard of 15% in the Carbon Emissions Reduction Obligation (CERO) of the current ECO scheme. In addition, the scoring mechanism under ECO is such that it incentivises delivery of measures in properties off the gas grid. Early next year we intend to consult on proposals for the future Energy Company Obligation which are expected to run from October 2018 to March 2022. The consultation will include proposals on rural delivery and on moving to a 100% focus on vulnerable and low income households.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","119281 ; 119286","2017-12-19T14:01:54.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806081/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806081/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806081/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-13","Energy Companies Obligation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what plans he has further to strengthen rural safeguards in the Carbon Savings Community obligation.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","119284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806082","Cabinet Office","false","2017-12-19","<p>The Electoral Commission has a statutory role to provide guidance to Electoral Registration Officers and Returning Officers. It is working closely with the Information Commissioner's Office, the Association of Electoral Administrators, the Society of Local Authority Chief Executives and the Scottish Assessors Association to develop guidance on the impact of the General Data Protection Regulation and the Data Protection Bill currently being considered in the House of Lords on the electoral administration responsibilities of Registration Officers and Returning Officers.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-12-19T15:02:16.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806082/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806082/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806082/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-12-13","Elections: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what assessment he has made of the effect of the EU General Data Protection Regulation on the roles and responsibilities of Electoral Registration Officers and Returning Officers; and what steps the Government is taking to communicate the effect of such changes to Returning Officers, Electoral Registration Officers and their staff.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","119285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806083","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-19","<p>Since 1 April 2017, the Carbon Savings Community Obligation is no longer part of the Energy Company Obligation (ECO). However, we introduced a rural safeguard of 15% in the Carbon Emissions Reduction Obligation (CERO) of the current ECO scheme. In addition, the scoring mechanism under ECO is such that it incentivises delivery of measures in properties off the gas grid. Early next year we intend to consult on proposals for the future Energy Company Obligation which are expected to run from October 2018 to March 2022. The consultation will include proposals on rural delivery and on moving to a 100% focus on vulnerable and low income households.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","119281 ; 119284","2017-12-19T14:01:54.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806083/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806083/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806083/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-13","Energy: Conservation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether he has plans to reduce the potential cost of energy efficiency schemes to off-gas-grid households in rural areas.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","119286"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806084","Department of Health","false","2017-12-18","<p>The Mental Health Crisis Care Concordat Steering Group last met on 6 September 2016 and the next meeting will take place on 10 January 2018.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-12-18T16:57:28.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806084/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806084/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806084/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-13","Crisis Care Concordat Steering Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when the Mental Health Crisis Care Concordat steering group last met; and when he plans to convene that steering group's next meeting.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","119287"
