"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806091","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-20","<p>This information is not available. The nationalities of staff that join the Department are checked as part of usual recruitment processes but that information is not thereafter collated centrally and it would be above the cost threshold to do so.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-12-20T15:09:17.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806091/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806091/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806091/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-13","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many non-UK EU nationals started employment in his Department since 23 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","119294"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806092","Department of Health","false","2017-12-21","<p>The Civil Service does not routinely collect information on the nationality of civil servants. The information is not held.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-12-21T16:15:07.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806092/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806092/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806092/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-13","Department of Health: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many non-UK EU nationals started employment in his Department since 23 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","119295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806093","Department for Education","false","2017-12-19","<p>All government departments are bound by legal requirements concerning the right to work in the UK and, in addition, the Civil Service Nationality Rules. Evidence of nationality is checked at the point of recruitment into the Civil Service as part of wider pre-employment checks, but there is no requirement on departments to retain this information beyond the point at which it has served its purpose.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-19T20:10:54.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806093/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806093/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806093/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-13","Department for Education: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many non-UK EU nationals started employment in his Department since 23 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","119296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806094","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-21","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 17 October 2016 to Question 47411 to the hon. Member for Birmingham, Selly Oak (Mr McCabe).</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-12-21T15:02:17.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806094/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806094/answer","20161017_WQnA_extract_in_MOD_Migrant_Workers.docx","20161017_WQnA_extract_in_MOD_Migrant_Workers.docx","47411 - MOD Migrant Workers","47411 - MOD Migrant Workers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806094/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-13","Ministry of Defence: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many non-UK EU nationals started employment in his Department since 23 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","119297"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806095","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-21","<p>​The Aliens' Employment Act 1955 makes it a requirement that all UK-based staff in the Foreign and Commonwealth Office must be British nationals or dual nationals where one of those nationalities is British. We do not centrally hold details of the nationality of our staff who are dual nationals.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-12-21T08:54:29.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806095/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806095/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806095/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-13","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many non-UK EU nationals started employment in his Department since 23 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","119298"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806096","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-18","<p>Since 23 June 2016, where nationality is recorded, 43 non-UK EU nationals on the payroll have started with Defra up to 30 November 2017.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-12-18T16:24:35.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806096/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806096/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806096/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-13","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many non-UK EU nationals started employment in his Department since 23 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","119299"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806097","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-21","<p>The Civil Service does not routinely collect information on the nationality of Civil Servants.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-12-21T13:32:38.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806097/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806097/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806097/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-13","Department for Transport: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many non-UK EU nationals started employment in his Department since 23 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","119300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806098","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-20","<p>We are unable to calculate how many non-UK EU nationals started employment since 2016 as we do not hold data on employee’s nationality. We have no legal or business requirement to do so.</p><p> </p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-12-20T11:16:51.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806098/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806098/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806098/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-13","Ministry of Justice: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many non-UK EU nationals started employment in his Department since 23 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","119301"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806099","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-21","<p>Thirteen non-UK EU nationals started employment in HM Treasury since 23<sup>rd</sup> June 2016.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-12-21T13:28:38.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806099/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806099/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806099/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-13","Treasury: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many non-UK EU nationals started employment in his Department since 23 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","119302"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806100","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-18","<p>We do not know how many non-UK EU nationals started employment in the Department for Work and Pensions, since 23 June 2016.</p><p> </p><p>Evidence of nationality is checked at the point of recruitment into the Civil Service, as part of wider pre-employment checks. But, there is no requirement on departments to retain this information, beyond the point at which it has served its purpose.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-12-18T17:39:49.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806100/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806100/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806100/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-13","Department for Work and Pensions: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many non-UK EU nationals started employment in his Department since 23 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","119303"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806102","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-12-21","We do not record the number of non-UK EU nationals who started employment in the Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, since 23 June 2016.<p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-12-21T17:10:43.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806102/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806102/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806102/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-12-13","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many non-UK EU nationals started employment in her Department since 23 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","119304"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806104","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-19","<p>The Department collects national identity data from its employees on a voluntary basis. Where staff self-describe their national identity as 'other' there is no requirement to provide further detail or evidence of their nationality. As such we are unable to accurately determine the number of non-UK EU nationals that have started in the Department in the time since 23 June 2016.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-12-19T14:16:32.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806104/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806104/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806104/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-12-13","Department for Communities and Local Government: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many non-UK EU nationals started employment in his Department since 23 June 2016.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","119305"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806105","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-21","<p>​The Government works in conjunction with Arctic Indigenous peoples towards a safe and secure Arctic, including through the Arctic Council. Foreign and Commonwealth Office officials recently heard the concerns of some of the Arctic’s Indigenous peoples at the “Arctic Voices” event hosted by the All Party Parliamentary Group for the Polar Regions. The UK remains of the view that only responsible development should take place in the Arctic region.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-12-21T09:56:34.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806105/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806105/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/806105/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-13","Arctic","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations his Department has received from Arctic Indigenous peoples on his proposed revised Arctic Policy Framework.","false","Biography information for James Gray","North Wiltshire","James Gray","119306"
